If you still haven’t quite had enough of YouTube’s most popular video of all time, try this for a tribute.

A French artist has created an astonishing flipbook version of Gangnam Style by South Korean rapper Psy, showing scenes from the music video that has racked up more than 1.2billion views.

The YouTube user, named ‘etoilec1’, produced the video by drawing the scenes in colour on a large flipbook and flicked through them for the four-minute clip, which has had more than 100,000 views.

