The artist also has produced flipbook videos for Dragon Ball Z, a popular Japanese series that ran from 1989 to 2003 and featured Earth's defender Goku protecting the planet from alien enemies.

Gangnam Style by South Korean rapper Psy became the first video to get more than 1billion views on YouTube - making it not only the most viewed, but also the most liked in the history of the website.

The song has made the artist - real name Park Jae-sang, 35 - famous worldwide and saw tourism in the Asian nation increase by 13 per cent last year with Seoul visitors going on ‘Gangnam tours’.

The song mocks the upmarket area of Seoul called Gangnam, where the city’s glitterati gather in cocktail bars and young shoppers spend their money in vintage clothes shops and designer outlets.

